The Warra Tall Eucalypt SuperSite was established in 2012 and is located in a stand of tall, mixed-aged &lt;em&gt;Eucalyptus obliqua&lt;/em&gt; forest (1.5, 77 and &gt;250 years-old) with a rainforest / wet sclerophyll understorey and a dense man-fern (&lt;em&gt;Dicksonia antarctica&lt;/em&gt;) ground-layer. The site experienced a fire in January 2019, which consumed the ground layer and killed a high proportion of the understorey trees but stimulated dense seedling regeneration. For additional site information, see https://www.tern.org.au/tern-observatory/tern-ecosystem-processes/warra-tall-eucalypt-supersite/.
